'''The Bridgestone''' Guides are independent guides to [[Ireland|Irish]] food and hospitality sponsored by [[Bridgestone]].<ref>[http://www.bridgestone.ie/bridgestone-guides Bridgestone Ireland - Guides] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310103547/http://www.bridgestone.ie/bridgestone-guides |date=March 10, 2012 }} (accessed 2012-03-16)</ref> Written and edited by John McKenna and his wife Sally,<ref name="Biblio">{{cite web|url=http://www.bibliocook.com/2010/04/the-bridgestone.html|title=The Bridgestone Irish Food Guide by John & Sally McKenna|publisher=Bibliocook|date=27 April 2010|accessdate=29 November 2010}}</ref> the guides have won [[André Simon (wine)|André Simon]], [[Glenfiddich]] and [[Slow Food]] awards.<ref name="amazon">{{Cite book|title=Bridgestone 100 Best Places to Stay 2006|publisher=[[Amazon (website)|Amazon]]|id= {{ASIN|1874076715|country=uk}}}}</ref> Prints include the ''Bridgestone Irish Food Guide'',<ref name="Biblio"/> The ''Bridgestone 100 Best Restaurants in Ireland 2011''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestofbridgestone.com/books|title=The Bridgestone Guides|publisher=Official website|accessdate=29 November 2010}}</ref> and The ''Bridgestone 100 Best Places to Stay in Ireland 2010''.<ref name="amazon"/>
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links== * [http://www.bridgestoneguides.com Bridgestone Guides Official website] * [https://web.archive.org/web/20111220103040/http://www.rte.ie/ten/2007/0810/bridgestone.html Book review] [[RTÉ]]
[[Category:Restaurant guides]]
{{travel-book-stub}}

{{Infobox museum | name = Chambas Municipal Museum | native_name = Museo Municipal de Chambas | native_name_lang = Spanish | image = | imagesize = | caption = | coordinates = | established = {{Start date|1982|12|29|df=y}} | location = [[Chambas]], [[Cuba]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Chambas Municipal Museum''' is a [[museum]] located in [[Chambas]], [[Cuba]]. It was established on 29 December 1982.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnpc.cult.cu/institucion/558|title=Museo Municipal de Chambas|publisher=Portal del Consejo Nacional de Patrimonio Cultural|accessdate=2015-11-01}}</ref>
The museum holds collections on archeology, history, ethnology and natural sciences.
== See also == * [[List of museums in Cuba]]
== References == {{Reflist}}
== External links == * {{ecured|Museo Municipal de Chambas}}
{{coord missing|Cuba}}
