{{italic title}} '''''The Almanac of American History''''' (1983) (revised edition 2004) is a [[reference work]] on [[History of the United States|American history]] in [[chronology]] format. Its general editor is [[Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr.]], and the executive editor is [[John S. Bowman]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr.|first1=(general editor)|title=The Almanac of American history|date=2004|publisher=Barnes & Noble Books|location=New York|isbn=978-0760756799|edition=Rev. and updated}}</ref>
Schlesinger wrote the introduction; in the current edition the introduction to each of the six sections is written by a different noted scholar:
*"Founding a Nation" (986-1787)&ndash;[[Gordon S. Wood]] ([[Brown University]]) *"Testing a Union" (1788-1865)&ndash;[[Marcus Cunliffe]] ([[George Washington University]]) *"Forging a Nation" (1866-1900)&ndash;[[S.L. Mayer]] ([[University of Southern California]]) *"Expanding Resources" (1901-1945)&ndash;[[Richard C. Wade]] ([[City University of New York]]) *"Emerging as a World Power" (1946-1999)&ndash;[[Robert H. Ferrell]] ([[Indiana University]]) *"Facing the Next Century" (2000-)&ndash;[[Rodney P. Carlisle]] ([[Rutgers University]])
